#: ipres.election_round.DrawLotsStrategy:1 of
msgid ""
"Strategy for breaking ties between two contestants across three "
"consecutive rounds."
msgstr ""

#: ipres.election_round.DrawLotsStrategy:3 of
msgid ""
"MARGINAL_LEAD: Award the win to the contestant with the higher vote "
"count in the most recent ballot round."
msgstr ""

#: ipres.election_round.DrawLotsStrategy:5 of
msgid "RANDOM: Break ties by uniform random selection (drawing of lots)."
msgstr ""

#: ipres.election_round.ElectionRound:1 of
msgid "Abstract base class for a single round within an iterative election."
msgstr ""

#: ipres.election_round.ElectionRound:3 of
msgid ""
"An election consists of one or more rounds. Each round either produces a "
"winner (the contestant whose vote share meets the super-majority "
"threshold) or reduces the field of contestants for the next round."
msgstr ""

#: ipres.election_round.ElectionRound:7 of
msgid "Two concrete subtypes exist:"
msgstr ""

#: ipres.election_round.ElectionRound:9 of
msgid ":class:`~ipres.ballot.Ballot` — a round decided by actual votes."
msgstr ""

#: ipres.election_round.ElectionRound:10 of
msgid ""
":class:`~ipres.draw_of_lots.DrawOfLots` — a round decided by lot when two"
" contestants are tied across three consecutive ballot rounds."
msgstr ""

#: ipres.election_round.ElectionRound:13 of
msgid ""
"Polymorphism via :meth:`getContestantsVotesAfterPossibleCoalitions` is "
"the key mechanism: ``Ballot`` reads from its own "
":class:`~ipres.vote_matrix.VoteMatrix`, while ``DrawOfLots`` delegates to"
" the previous round."
msgstr ""

#: ipres.election_round.ElectionRound.getContestants:1 of
msgid ""
"Return the current contestants, including any coalitions formed after the"
" round."
msgstr ""

#: ipres.election_round.ElectionRound.getContestantsVotesAfterPossibleCoalitions:1
#: of
msgid ""
"Return vote totals for each current contestant, merging coalition member "
"votes."
msgstr ""

#: ipres.election_round.ElectionRound.getContestantsVotesAfterPossibleCoalitions:3
#: of
msgid ""
"For :class:`~ipres.ballot.Ballot`, totals come from its own vote matrix. "
"For :class:`~ipres.draw_of_lots.DrawOfLots`, totals are delegated to the "
"previous ballot round."
msgstr ""

#: ipres.election_round.ElectionRound.getNextRoundInput:1 of
msgid ""
"Return the pre-built input for the next round, or ``None`` if the "
"election is finished."
msgstr ""

#: ipres.election_round.ElectionRound.getNextRoundInput:3 of
msgid ""
"Always ``None`` for :class:`~ipres.draw_of_lots.DrawOfLots` (which is "
"always terminal)."
msgstr ""

#: ipres.election_round.ElectionRound.getOriginalContestants:1 of
msgid ""
"Return the contestants as they were at the start of this round, before "
"coalition formation."
msgstr ""

#: ipres.election_round.ElectionRound.getParticipatingParties:1 of
msgid "Return the names of all original parties taking part in this round."
msgstr ""

#: ipres.election_round.ElectionRound.getParticipatingParties:3 of
msgid "For coalition contestants, each member party is listed individually."
msgstr ""

#: ipres.election_round.ElectionRound.getPreviousRound:1 of
msgid "Return the preceding round, or ``None`` if this is the first round."
msgstr ""

#: ipres.election_round.ElectionRound.getRoundNumber:1 of
msgid "Return the 1-based index of this round within the election."
msgstr ""

#: ipres.election_round.ElectionRound.getWinner:1 of
msgid "Return the winning contestant, or ``None`` if no winner was found."
msgstr ""

#: ipres.election_round.ElectionRound.hasNext:1 of
msgid ""
"Return ``True`` if the election continues with another round after this "
"one."
msgstr ""

#: ipres.election_round.ElectionRound.hasWinner:1 of
msgid "Return ``True`` if a winner was determined in this round."
msgstr ""

